 building sector, ridge tiles play a crucial role in ensuring the structural integrity of large-scale roofing systems. These applications often involve commercial buildings such as offices, retail spaces, warehouses, and industrial facilities. The commercial sector’s demand for ridge tiles is typically driven by the need for robust, long-lasting roofing solutions that can withstand diverse weather conditions while offering aesthetic value. As commercial buildings are built to last for decades, the quality of materials used, including ridge tiles, is critical. Builders and developers prioritize ridge tiles that offer high durability and can contribute to the building’s overall energy efficiency, aligning with green building standards.</p><p>The rising trend in commercial construction, including the development of mixed-use spaces and commercial complexes, has created increased demand for high-performance ridge tiles. Commercial buildings also require roofing solutions that are easy to maintain, durable, and capable of withstanding larger volumes of foot traffic compared to residential roofs. The growing focus on sustainable construction practices within commercial buildings has further influenced the demand for ridge tiles. As businesses and property owners seek to reduce operational costs through energy-efficient designs, the application of ridge tiles that contribute to better insulation and climate control has become a significant trend within the commercial building market.</p><h2>Other</h2><p>The 'Other' segment in the ridge tile market encompasses a variety of applications beyond residential and commercial buildings. These may include applications in industrial settings, agricultural buildings, public infrastructure, and even in artistic or decorative uses. Ridge tiles in this category are often customized for specific needs, offering versatility in terms of design, material composition, and functionality. Industrial buildings, for example, may require ridge ti